This Readme was wroten by Camilo Campos <zeromaisum@gmail.com> and explans how to make a package .deb of BRisa UPnP framework
This package was made using the Ubuntu 9.10 Karmic Koala and the kernel 2.6.31-22-generic

The first step is changing the name of the folder qt-brisa to brisa2.0 then this folder should be moved to "/home/username/brisa-2.0/usr/lib".
The second step is create a folder "DEBIAN" in "/home/username/brisa-2.0" and the files: 

"control" whose content is 

Source: libbrisa
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Camilo Campos <zeromaisum@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5.0.38), libqt4-dev
Standards-Version: 3.8.2
Package: libbrisa-dev
Architecture: all
Section: devel
Depends: libqt4-dev
version:2.0
Description: A C++ UPnP library.



postinst whose content is 

#! /bin/bash

echo "Instaling BRisa UPnP"
cd /usr/lib/brisa-2.0
./configure
make 
make install
echo "Instalation finished"
exit 0



rules whose content is 

#!/usr/bin/make -f

include /usr/share/cdbs/1/class/qmake.mk
include /usr/share/cdbs/1/rules/debhelper.mk



the trird step is go to the shell change the directory to "/home/username/brisa-2.0" and type "dpkg -b brisa-2.0" then the package brisa-2.0.deb will be created.

